cell("markdown","---\n## Phase 3 — Olympiad Extension\n\n### Challenge: Quadratic Encoding\nSuppose the encoding function was $f(x) = ax^2 + bx + c$, with $a,b,c \\in [0, 20]$.\nTo decode, you must use the Quadratic Formula! \nWrite a brute-force solver that searches for $a,b,c$ and uses the quadratic formula to decode. Remember that the quadratic formula yields two roots; at least one must be a valid character index.\n\n*(Leave as a theoretical exercise or implement below if you dare!)*"),
