cell("markdown","### Chalkboard Defense\nWhat is the time complexity of the brute force search in terms of the message length $L$ and the search range $R$ for the parameters $a$ and $b$? Why does brute-force cryptography fail on modern AES-256?\n\n<details><summary>💡 Sketch</summary>\nThe two loops take $O(R^2)$ iterations. Inside the loop, decoding takes $O(L)$. Total time is $O(L \\cdot R^2)$.\nModern AES-256 has $R = 2^{256}$. $O(R)$ is so astronomically large that all the computers on Earth couldn't check every combination before the heat death of the universe.\n</details>\n\n---\n📚 **Next:** Algorithms 08 (Backtracking & Magic Squares)")
