cell("markdown","---\n## Phase 3 — Olympiad Extension\n\n### Challenge: Recursive Backtracking\nWriting 9 nested loops is ugly. Writing 16 nested loops for a $4 \\times 4$ square is unbearable!\nWe can generalize backtracking using **Recursion**. Write a recursive solver that takes `(square, index)` and tries to fill `index` from 1 to 9, calling itself for `index+1`."),
cell("code","def solve_recursive(square, index=0):\n    '''Recursively fill the square. Return True if solved.'''\n    # YOUR CODE HERE\n    pass"),
cell("markdown","### Chalkboard Defense\nWhy is recursive backtracking a form of Depth-First Search (DFS) on a tree? Draw a tiny tree showing the pruning of branches.\n\n<details><summary>💡 Sketch</summary>\nThe search space is a tree where the root is an empty board, and each child adds one number. Exploring deeply until hitting a wall (hopeless) and then stepping back to try the next sibling is exactly Depth-First Search. Pruning a node deletes the entire subtree below it.\n</details>\n\n---\n📚 **Next:** Algorithms 09 (Estimating Roots)")
