cell("markdown","### Pathological Case: Newton's Nightmare\nNewton-Raphson is fast, but it can fail spectacularly. Consider $f(x) = x^{1/3}$.\nIts derivative is $\\frac{1}{3}x^{-2/3}$. \nThe update rule becomes $x_{n+1} = x_n - \\frac{x_n^{1/3}}{\\frac{1}{3}x_n^{-2/3}} = x_n - 3x_n = -2x_n$.\nIf you start at $x_0 = 1$, the guesses are $1, -2, 4, -8, 16 \\dots$ it spirals to infinity!\n\nWrite a test showing this divergence."),
